      "role": "user",
      "content": "the thing is it wasn't just a \"trick of the light.\" it was too precise. like the computer hasn't rendered the textures properly. and then the sun hit the asphalt and for a second the shadow of the tree didn't even make sense, it looked pixelated or something. it's making me feel really uneasy because it feels like the world is just... thin. like there's something behind it. do you think it's possible we're living in a simulation and the hardware is just struggling to keep up?",
